CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 10, 1946, pg. 8 reads: "Chatting - Loendi Club and the Frogs' Wives coffee hour drew this trio of charm to the salon for an hour of pleasant chatter. Left, is Miss Gladys Wylie of New York, relative of the W. G. Nunns, who houseguested with them; center, Mrs. A.L. Taylor of Dayton, wife of the eminent doctor, who is stopping with Henri and Hattie Vaughn and being highly entertained; right, Mrs. Stanley Williams, wife of the well known business man of Pittsburgh, whose charming home has been opened for many visitors during Frog Week. - Harris Photo"
TitMainTitle: Gladys Wylie, Mrs. A. L. Taylor, and Mrs. Stanley Williams standing in Loendi Club for FROGS wives coffee hour event
